                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.52/619: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-05-14T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 14, 1921—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>65. Your despatch 3847, April 30th, Agrarian Bill.<note n="97" xml:id="d414fn97"
                        >Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Consulate San Luis Potosi reports Bill has passed and Act now in force.</p>
                <pb facs="0587" n="491" xml:id="pg_491"/>
                <p>Informally request appropriate authorities to advise you whether such is the case
                    and take occasion to renew informal protest made pursuant Department’s 54, April
                    20th, 6 p.m., adding that this Government will not consent to the application of
                    the attempted confiscatory provisions of this measure to American citizens
                    owning land acquired in accordance with Mexican law.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
